{
  "text": "Definition 2.8 (Transaction Collection Strategy). The transaction collection strategy refers to the mining pool's strategy for collecting unconfirmed transactions into a new block. Many factors [CITATION_1] , [CITATION_2] affect it such as waiting time, transaction size and transaction fees. We will further discuss the transaction collection strategy in section 5.2.",
  "correct_citation": {
